== Events == * In the 1st year of the Yōrō era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[717]] {{ill|December 24|ja|12月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Because Emperor Genshō went on a royal progress and named the falls at Yōrō, the era name was changed to Yōrō from Reiki. * In the 1st year of the Shōryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1077]] {{ill|December 5|ja|12月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from Enpō to Shōryaku. * In the 1st year of the Bunji era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|December 10|ja|12月10日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The beloved concubine of Minamoto no Yoshitsune, who had parted ways with him on Mount Yoshino, was captured by forces of the Kamakura shogunate. * In the 8th year of the Kōan era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1285]] {{ill|December 14|ja|12月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the Shimotsuki Incident, due to slander by the internal administrator Hira Yoritada, the regent (Shikken) Hojo Sadatoki exterminated the clan of his external relative Adachi Yasamori, establishing a regime of regency rule. * In the 2nd year of the Shōhō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1646]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The honorific title "Tōshō" was conferred upon Nikkō Tōshō-sha.
== Births ==
== Deaths == * In the 7th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1836]] {{ill|December 24|ja|12月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Iizuka Igana, an inventor (born 1762). * In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Nakaoka Shintarō, a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born 1838).
