[[de:November 17 (Lunisolar)]] [[sn:November 17 (Lunisolar)]] [[ko:음력 11월 17일]] [[ja:11月17日 (旧暦)]] [[zh:十一月十七]] [[en:draft:November 17 (Lunisolar)]] [[en:11月17日 (旧暦)]] [[sn:ovember 17 (Lunisolar)]] [[ar:November 17 (Lunisolar)]]

{{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 17''' is the 17th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=}}.
== Events == * In the 1st year of the Yōrō era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|en|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|qq=}} [[717]] {{ill|December 24|ja|12月24日|qq=}}) – Because Emperor Genshō went on a royal progress and named the falls at Yōrō, the era name was changed to Yōrō from Reiki. * In the 1st year of the Shōryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|en|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|qq=}} [[1077]] {{ill|December 5|ja|12月5日|qq=}}) – The era name was changed from Enpō to Shōryaku. * In the 1st year of the Bunji era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|en|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|qq=}} [[1185]] {{ill|December 10|ja|12月10日|qq=}}) – The beloved concubine of Minamoto no Yoshitsune, who had parted ways with him on Mount Yoshino, was captured by forces of the Kamakura shogunate. * In the 8th year of the Kōan era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|en|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|qq=}} [[1285]] {{ill|December 14|ja|12月14日|qq=}}) – During the Shimotsuki Incident, due to slander by the internal administrator Hira Yoritada, the regent (Shikken) Hojo Sadatoki exterminated the clan of his external relative Adachi Yasamori, establishing a regime of regency rule. * In the 2nd year of the Shōhō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|qq=}} [[1646]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|qq=}}) – The honorific title "Tōshō" was conferred upon Nikkō Tōshō-sha.
== Births ==
== Deaths == * In the 7th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|qq=}} [[1836]] {{ill|December 24|ja|12月24日|qq=}}) – Iizuka Igana, an inventor (born 1762). * In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|qq=}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|qq=}}) – Nakaoka Shintarō, a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born 1838).
== Commemorations == * Shiro Shogi – A castle shogi tournament held from the time of Tokugawa Yoshimune until the collapse of the Tokugawa shogunate.
