ys with him on Mount Yoshino, was captured by forces of the Kamakura shogunate. * In the 8th year of the Kōan era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|en|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|zh|儒略曆|fr|Calendrier_julien|es|Calendario_juliano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1285]] {{ill|December 14|ja|12月14日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – During the Shimotsuki Incident, due to slander by the internal administrator Hira Yoritada, the regent (Shikken) Hojo Sadatoki exterminated the clan of his external relative Adachi Yasamori, establishing a regime of regency rule. * In the 2nd year of the Shōhō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1646]] {{ill|January 3|ja|1月3日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – The honorific title "Tōshō" was conferred upon Nikkō Tōshō-sha.
== Births ==
== Deaths == * In the 7th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1836]] {{ill|December 24|ja|12月24日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – Iizuka Igana, an inventor (born 1762). * In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|en|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|公历|fr|Calendrier_grégorien|es|Calendario_gregoriano|qq=|qq=draft}} [[1867]] {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|qq=|qq=draft}}) – Nakaoka Shintarō, a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born 1838).
== Commemorations == * Shiro Shogi – A castle shogi tournament held from the time of Tokugawa Yoshimune until the collapse of the Tokugawa shogunate.
