'''November 17''' is the 17th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} is {{ill|Senbu|WD=Q96759842|1=senpu}}{{efn|ja|先負|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* In the 1st year of the Yōrō era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|717|en|717|WD=Q23532|lt=717|1=717}} {{ill|December 24|en|December 24|WD=Q2705|lt=December 24|1=December 24}}) – Because Emperor Genshō went on a royal progress and named the falls at Yōrō, the era name was changed to Yōrō from Reiki.
* In the 1st year of the Shōryaku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1077|en|1077|WD=Q19441|lt=1077|1=1077}} {{ill|December 5|en|December 5|WD=Q2300|lt=December 5|1=December 5}}) – The era name was changed from Enpō to Shōryaku.
* In the 1st year of the Bunji era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1185|en|1185|WD=Q19729|lt=1185|1=1185}} {{ill|December 10|en|December 10|WD=Q2302|lt=December 10|1=December 10}}) – The beloved concubine of Minamoto no Yoshitsune, who had parted ways with him on Mount Yoshino, was captured by forces of the Kamakura shogunate.
* In the 8th year of the Kōan era ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1285|en|1285|WD=Q5546|lt=1285|1=1285}} {{ill|December 14|en|December 14|WD=Q2382|lt=December 14|1=December 14}}) – During the Shimotsuki Incident, due to slander by the internal administrator Hira Yoritada, the regent (Shikken) Hojo Sadatoki exterminated the clan of his external relative Adachi Yasamori, establishing a regime of regency rule.
* In the 2nd year of the Shōhō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1646|en|1646|WD=Q6930|lt=1646|1=1646}} {{ill|January 3|en|January 3|WD=Q2156|lt=January 3|1=January 3}}) – The honorific title "Tōshō" was conferred upon Nikkō Tōshō-sha.

== Births ==

== Deaths ==
* In the 7th year of the Tenpō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1836|en|1836|WD=Q7601|lt=1836|1=1836}} {{ill|December 24|en|December 24|WD=Q2705|lt=December 24|1=December 24}}) – Iizuka Igana, an inventor (born 1762).
* In the 3rd year of the Keiō era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1867|en|1867|WD=Q7715|lt=1867|1=1867}} {{ill|December 12|en|December 12|WD=Q2369|lt=December 12|1=December 12}}) – Nakaoka Shintarō, a proponent of Sonnō jōi (born 1838).

== Commemorations ==
* Shiro Shogi – A castle shogi tournament held from the time of Tokugawa Yoshimune until the collapse of the Tokugawa shogunate.

